<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-11"><hi rend="italic">August 11,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Powell reports that the <hi rend="italic">D’Assas</hi> has returned;
                            brings news that Petit Goave is entirely destroyed; 10,000 people
                            homeless; foreigners at coffee usine; the <hi rend="italic">D’Assas</hi>
                            brought 150 women and children to Port au Prince; that Killick blockades
                            Cape, refusing the <hi rend="italic">Paloma</hi> entrance on August
                            10.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Powell has instructed Consul Livingston to ignore the blockade.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>